---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About" description="About Varun Nair — Solutions Architect, Java developer, telecoms specialist.">

  <div class="container page-wrap">

    <header class="page-header fade-up">
      <p class="page-eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Varun Nair</h1>
      <p class="page-sub">Solutions Architect & Software Developer</p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-grid fade-up fade-up-1">

      <aside class="about-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <p class="sidebar-label">Based in</p>
          <p>Zoetermeer, Netherlands</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <p class="sidebar-label">Currently at</p>
          <p>KPN via Prodapt</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <p class="sidebar-label">Links</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/VarunDelft" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="sidebar-link">GitHub ↗</a>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/varunnair1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="sidebar-link">LinkedIn ↗</a>
          <a href="https://twitter.com/Var92" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="sidebar-link">Twitter ↗</a>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <p class="sidebar-label">Certifications</p>
          <p class="sidebar-cert">AWS Solutions Architect – Associate</p>
          <p class="sidebar-cert">OCI AI Foundations 2025</p>
          <p class="sidebar-cert">Hands-On AI: LLM-Powered Apps</p>
          <p class="sidebar-cert">ELK Stack + Filebeat Masterclass</p>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="about-body prose">
        <p>
          I'm a Solutions Architect with over a decade of experience in the telecommunications
          and connectivity domain. Over the years I've moved between roles — researcher,
          business analyst, consultant, solution designer, pre-sales lead, DevOps engineer,
          and hands-on developer. The thread connecting all of them is a preference for
          being close to the work rather than directing it from a distance.
        </p>
        <p>
          What drives me is the full product lifecycle: the design conversation, writing
          the code, shipping it, and keeping it healthy in production. I think of this as
          having "skin in the game" — the kind of involvement that makes better decisions
          possible because you can't ignore the consequences of them.
        </p>
        <p>
          My core technical background is Java (Spring Boot, microservices), cloud infrastructure
          on AWS, and the operational side of telecom systems: network provisioning, orchestration,
          assurance, and the standards — TMF, 3GPP, MEF — that sit underneath them. More recently
          I've been spending time with Generative AI and exploring what agentic approaches
          can realistically do for network automation.
        </p>
        <p>
          I did my M.Sc. in Electrical Engineering (Telecommunications & Sensing Systems)
          at TU Delft, which is also how I ended up in the Netherlands. Before that,
          a B.Tech in Electronics & Communications from Delhi College of Engineering,
          and some early-career time at Reliance Jio in Mumbai.
        </p>

        <h2>Outside work</h2>
        <p>
          I read a lot — history, geopolitics, technology writing, science fiction.
          <em>The Three-Body Problem</em> remains a favourite. For balance: hiking,
          cycling, tennis, and the occasional swim.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <hr />

    <section class="stats-row fade-up fade-up-2">
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-n">10+</span>
        <span class="stat-l">Years experience</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-n">5+</span>
        <span class="stat-l">Operators worked with</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-n">5</span>
        <span class="stat-l">Certifications</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-n">3</span>
        <span class="stat-l">Published papers</span>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</Base>

<style>
.page-wrap { padding: 5rem 0 4rem; }
.page-header { margin-bottom: 4rem; }
.page-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.page-header h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
.page-sub { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--ink-tertiary); }

.about-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
}
.about-sidebar { position: sticky; top: calc(var(--nav-h) + 2rem); }
.sidebar-block { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.sidebar-label {
  font-size: 0.68rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.07em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}
.sidebar-block p { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--ink-secondary); }
.sidebar-link {
  display: block;
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  color: var(--ink-secondary);
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}
.sidebar-cert {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--ink-tertiary);
  line-height: 1.5;
  margin-bottom: 0.3rem !important;
}

.stats-row {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  gap: 2rem;
  padding: 3rem 0 0;
}
.stat { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.3rem; }
.stat-n {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: 2.2rem;
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1;
}
.stat-l { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--ink-tertiary); }

@media (max-width: 680px) {
  .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
  .about-sidebar { position: static; }
  .stats-row { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
}
</style>
